[normal]4.1 
[normal]Many of The Post Office’s financial service products are provided in partnership with the Bank of Ireland and the two companies have built a successful partnership over the past decade
[normal]. 
[normal]Together we provide a comprehensive range of 
[normal]products to 3 million customers and we have a savings book valued at £17 billion.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]4.2 
[normal]The Bank of Ireland’s UK business was incorporated into a separate ring-fenced UK company on 1 November 2010 which means that depositors are protected under the 
[normal]Financia
[normal]l Services Compensation Scheme (FSCS).
